  "text": "Caching at exit nodes: Perhaps each exit node should run a caching web proxy [CITATION_1] , to improve anonymity for cached pages (Alice's request never leaves the Tor network), to improve speed, and to reduce bandwidth cost. On the other hand, forward security is weakened because caches constitute a record of retrieved files. We must find the right balance between usability and security.",
